    <item>
      <title>Joel 1</title>
      <link>http://localhost:58357/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/joel/chapter-01/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:58357/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/joel/chapter-01/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;joel-chapter-1&#34;&gt;Joel Chapter 1&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; A Message from the LORD to Joel Son of Pethuel&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v2&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; Listen to this, elders;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; Tell your descendants about it;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v4&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; What the cutting locusts left&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v5&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt; Wake up, you drunks, and cry;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v6&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;6&lt;/sup&gt; A nation has invaded my land,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v7&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;7&lt;/sup&gt; It&amp;rsquo;s destroyed my grapevines&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v8&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt; Wail like a virgin wearing burlap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v9&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; The grain offerings and liquid offerings have stopped&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v10&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;10&lt;/sup&gt; The fields are ruined, the land is bare&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Joel 2</title>
      <link>http://localhost:58357/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/joel/chapter-02/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:58357/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/joel/chapter-02/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;joel-chapter-2&#34;&gt;Joel Chapter 2&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; Blow a bugle in Zion;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; Fire consumes ahead of them;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v4&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; They look like horses;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v5&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt; With rumbling like chariots,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v6&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;6&lt;/sup&gt; Defenders are in anguish in front of them&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v7&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;7&lt;/sup&gt; They run like warriors&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v8&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt; They don&amp;rsquo;t bump into one another;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v9&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; They rush at the city and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v10&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;10&lt;/sup&gt; The ground quakes in front of them,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v11&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;11&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD raises his voice in front of his army;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Joel 3</title>
      <link>http://localhost:58357/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/joel/chapter-03/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:58357/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/joel/chapter-03/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;joel-chapter-3&#34;&gt;Joel Chapter 3&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; When I restore the fortunes of Judah and Jerusalem, 2I&amp;rsquo;ll gather the nations to the Valley of Jehoshaphat and condemn them there on behalf of Israel, my permanent possession, my people. They scattered them among the nations, divided up my land, 3cast lots for my people, traded a boy for a prostitute, and sold a girl for wine to get drunk on. 4&amp;quot;What are you to me, Tyre, Sidon, Philistia? You think you&amp;rsquo;re going to pay me back? If you try, I&amp;rsquo;ll return it on your head swift and soon. 5You&amp;rsquo;ve stolen my silver and gold, taken my precious treasures into your temples, 6and sold Judah and Jerusalem to the Greeks to remove them far away. 7So I&amp;rsquo;m going to raise them up from where you sold them and pay you back on your own head. 8I&amp;rsquo;ll sell your sons and daughters to Judah to sell to the Sabeans far away.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
